  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Airway inflammation is partly driven by Th17 and Th17-polarizing cytokines that is
      steroid-resistant. Statins could suppress IL-17 cytokines in other diseases such as
      atherosclerosis and multiple sclerosis in mouse model. The investigators hypothesize that
      statins might provide anti-inflammatory benefit of suppressing IL-17 cytokines in COPD
      patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
